    "Meanwhile, dialog-style instruction pairs are derived from MCQs to further enrich the training materials, as depicted in Figure 3.For urban planning textbooks, which primarily contain descriptive text without readily available instruction pairs, more data The city is an integrated giant system, which includes economic subsystems, political subsystems, social subsystems, spatial environment subsystems and factor flow subsystems.",
    "There is a very complex relationship between the elements that make up the urban system, which intertwine and overlap with each other, function together and respond to a certain extent to various human behaviors.",
    "instruction:Please briefly describe the components of the urban system.",
    "response:The urban system is an integrated giant system, including economic subsystems, political subsystems, social subsystems, spatial environment subsystems and factor flow subsystems.",
    "These subsystems have a complex relationship with each other, and together they contribute to the overall operation and development of the city."
